# The .map() Method

In JavaScript, `array.map()` creates a new array by calling a function on every element. In React, we use it to transform an array of data into an array of JSX elements.

## Basic Syntax

```jsx
const numbers = [1, 2, 3];
const listItems = numbers.map(number => 
  <li>{number}</li>
);

return <ul>{listItems}</ul>;
```

This will render an unordered list with three list items.
